Year = {2022},
Pages = {104-109},
Abstract = {Noxious comments are impolite, rude, profane, or disrespectful online
   comments that can result in restricting people from expressing their
   thoughts and views, and to stop seeking others' opinions because of the
   fear of harassment. Conversational toxicity is a snag that is making
   people uneasy and ultimately leading them to leave the discussion. This
   paper comprehensively examines the online abuse in text/comments and
   categorize the content into multi-label classification to study the
   toxicity as accurately as possible. Here, the impacts of Machine
   learning algorithms like Logistic regression, Naive Bayes, K-Nearest
   Neighbors (KNN), and Decision Tree have been studied and enforced to the
   facts to answer the troubles in textual categories, and the first-rate
   algorithm is chosen on the basis of metrics. Moving ahead, the work aims
   to achieve higher overall performance, and the levels of toxic content
   is studied for better accuracy to prevent its negative results which
   ultimately helps plenty of groups to inspect those issues.},
